The News Agency of Nigeria(NAN) reports that the president had presented a federal budget of N8.83 trillion for the 2019 fiscal year. The 2019 total budget estimate is N300 billion lower than the N9.1 billion being implemented for the current fiscal year. The sum of N4.04 trillion or 50.31 per cent is earmarked for Recurrent Expenditure, while N2.03 trillion representing 22.98 per cent is for capital projects.(NAN)